This project presents a comprehensive strategic optimization of the international service network for Cayman Airways Ltd. (CAL). As the national flag carrier, CAL must balance its social mandate to provide "life-line" connectivity with the financial necessity of maximizing network profitability. By applying Mixed-Integer Linear Programming (MILP) and Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP) modeling, we have identified a high-value configuration that optimizes the utilization of the Boeing 737-8 MAX fleet.
